# Translation properties formatting

After editing any file under `freeplane/resources/translations/` or `freeplane/viewer-resources/translations/`:

1. Do **not** rely on manual key order. New keys can be appended anywhere.
2. Run formatting before finishing:

```powershell
tools\apache-ant-1.10.14\bin\ant.bat -f freeplane\ant\build.xml format-translation
```

The build also auto-runs `format-translation` before `check-translation`, but formatting locally keeps git diffs clean and avoids surprise file reordering during CI/build.

Rules enforced by `FormatTranslation`:
- Keys sorted case-insensitively
- Duplicate keys removed (manual translation preferred over `[auto]` / `[translate me]`)
- Unix line endings (`\n`)
- Use `{0}`, `{1}` placeholders (not `$1`, `$2`)

Chinese text may stay as `\uXXXX` escapes or UTF-8; formatting preserves meaning.
